item.title: CVE-2023-30945|2024-08-02T14:37:15.582Z -- palantir -- com.palantir.gotham%3Aclips2
item.description: Multiple Services such as VHS(Video History Server) and VCD(Video Clip Distributor) and Clips2 were discovered to be vulnerable to an unauthenticated arbitrary file read/write vulnerability due to missing input validation on filenames. A malicious attacker could read sensitive files from the filesystem or write/delete arbitrary files on the filesystem as well.
